NDX:Try Simply Readable Scenario
=================================

This scenario deploys the Document Translation & Simply Readable application,
originally created by Swindon Borough Council and published as an AWS Sample.

Upstream Source
--------------
Repository: https://github.com/aws-samples/document-translation
Version:    v3.4.0 (commit 0cd1b4a)
License:    MIT-0 (MIT No Attribution)

The following components are built from the upstream source (cloned automatically
by the build scripts into .upstream/):

  - Lambda function zips (lambda/*.zip) - built by scripts/build-lambdas.js
  - React web application (website-build/) - built by scripts/build-website.js

CDK Infrastructure
------------------
The CDK constructs in cdk/lib/ are reimplemented for Innovation Sandbox (ISB)
compatibility. They follow the same architectural patterns as the upstream CDK
but are original works adapted for StackSet deployment, S3-hosted assets, and
ISB-specific requirements (no CDK bootstrap, account-agnostic bucket names).

Runtime Config Patch
--------------------
The upstream React app uses build-time config via require("../cfnOutputs.json").
The build-website.js script patches amplifyConfigure.tsx to load config at
runtime from window.__DOCTRAN_CONFIG__, populated by a CloudFormation Custom
Resource at deploy time. This allows the same build to work across multiple
sandbox accounts.
